# extract name from email-
john.doe@example.com to John DOe
=PROPER(SUBSTITUTE(LEFT(A2,FIND("@",A2)-1),"."," "))

1. FIND("@", A2)
What it does: Finds the position of @ in the email.
For john.doe@example.com, it returns 9, because @ is the 9th character.
 2. FIND("@", A2) - 1
We subtract 1 to stop just before the @.
So instead of extracting john.doe@, we get just john.doe.
3. LEFT(A2, FIND("@",A2)-1)
LEFT(text, number of characters) gets characters from the start.
This gives:
LEFT("john.doe@example.com", 8) → john.doe
4. SUBSTITUTE(..., ".", " ")
What it does: Replaces all dots . with spaces.
So: john.doe becomes john doe.


